<aside style="background-image: url(img/a02.jpg);">

	<blockquote>
		<p class="cite">In&nbsp;the 20th century, we&nbsp;stepped out from Earth: to&nbsp;Space, to&nbsp;the Moon, to&nbsp;the Solar System.</p>
		<p class="extra">In&nbsp;the 21st century, we&nbsp;will find out about life at&nbsp;the galactic scale. It&nbsp;is&nbsp;time to&nbsp;open our eyes and ears to&nbsp;the cosmos.</p>
	</blockquote>
	<p class="author">Yuri Milner</p>

</aside>

<main>

	<h1 class="mb-4">Publications</h1>

	<div class="mb-5">
		<p class="lead mb-3"><a href="https://www.scientificamerican.com/article/frank-drakes-courageous-questions-live-on/" target="_blank">Frank Drake&rsquo;s Courageous Questions Live&nbsp;On</a></p>
		<p>On&nbsp;September&nbsp;2, 2022, the astronomer Frank Drake passed away. Drake was a&nbsp;founding father of&nbsp;SETI and one of&nbsp;its most influential figures for sixty years. In&nbsp;2015. He&nbsp;stood alongside Yuri at&nbsp;London&rsquo;s Royal Society to&nbsp;launch Breakthrough Listen, and he&nbsp;was an&nbsp;esteemed a&nbsp;member of&nbsp;its Advisory Committee for seven years. Yuri wrote this obituary about him for <strong>Scientific American</strong>.</p>
	</div>

	<div class="mb-5">
		<p class="lead mb-3"><a href="https://forbes.co.il/%D7%9C%D7%94%D7%91%D7%99%D7%98-%D7%9E%D7%A2%D7%91%D7%A8-%D7%9C%D7%90%D7%95%D7%A4%D7%A7-%D7%99%D7%95%D7%A8%D7%99-%D7%9E%D7%99%D7%9C%D7%A0%D7%A8-%D7%9E%D7%9E%D7%99%D7%99%D7%A1%D7%93%D7%99-%D7%A4%D7%99/" target="_blank">Looking Beyond The Horizon (in&nbsp;Hebrew)</a></p>
		<p>In&nbsp;September 2020, Yuri wrote this article for <strong>Forbes Israel</strong>, about his motivations and hopes for the Friends of&nbsp;Israel MBA&nbsp;&ndash; a&nbsp;new fellowship at&nbsp;his alma mater, the Wharton School of&nbsp;Business, for Israeli students, which is&nbsp;sponsored by&nbsp;the foundation that he&nbsp;and his wife Julia established.</p>
	</div>

	<div class="mb-5">
		<p class="lead mb-3"><a href="https://www.calcalistech.com/ctech/articles/0,7340,L-3805618,00.html" target="_blank">Let&rsquo;s Mask Up&nbsp;&ndash; and Unmask the Power of&nbsp;Science</a></p>
		<p>In&nbsp;April 2020, Milner Foundation announced a&nbsp;donation of&nbsp;3&nbsp;million face masks for people of&nbsp;Israel. Yuri Milner in&nbsp;his open letter published by&nbsp;Calcalist wrote that &ldquo;a&nbsp;significant fraction of&nbsp;these masks will go&nbsp;to&nbsp;organizations providing essential services, whose frontline workers are still required to&nbsp;do&nbsp;their jobs during the lockdown&rdquo;.</p>
	</div>

	<div class="mb-5">
		<p class="lead mb-3"><a href="https://blogs.scientificamerican.com/observations/stephen-hawking-the-universe-does-not-forget-and-neither-will-we/" target="_blank">Stephen Hawking: The Universe Does Not Forget, and Neither Will We</a></p>
		<p class="mb-3">Scientific American 2018</p>
		<p>In&nbsp;March 2017, Stephen Hawking passed away. The world-famous cosmologist had been an&nbsp;inaugural winner of&nbsp;the Special Breakthrough Prize in&nbsp;Fundamental Physics; and he&nbsp;had partnered with Yuri in&nbsp;launching the Breakthrough Initiatives in&nbsp;2015, and Breakthrough Starshot in&nbsp;2016. Yuri wrote this obituary for Scientific American, dwelling on&nbsp;Hawking&rsquo;s greatness both as&nbsp;a&nbsp;physicist and as&nbsp;a&nbsp;man.</p>
	</div>

	<div class="mb-5">
		<p class="lead mb-3"><a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2016/12/06/opinion/this-years-game-changers-in-space.html" target="_blank">This Year&rsquo;s Game Changers in&nbsp;Space</a></p>
		<p class="mb-3">New York Times&nbsp;&ndash; Turning Points 2017</p>
		<p>The NYT&rsquo;s Turning Points explores what critical moments from this year might mean for the year ahead. In&nbsp;2017, Yuri contributed an&nbsp;article looking at&nbsp;some major scientific advances of&nbsp;the previous year&nbsp;&ndash; the discovery of&nbsp;an&nbsp;Earth-sized planet in&nbsp;our nearest star system, the genomic analysis of&nbsp;the last universal common ancestor, and the detection of&nbsp;gravitational waves&nbsp;&ndash; what they meant to&nbsp;him and how they can inspire&nbsp;us all.</p>
	</div>

	<div class="mb-5">
		<p class="lead mb-3"><a href="https://ukshop.economist.com/products/the-world-in-2017" target="_blank">May science go&nbsp;Gangnam</a> (Paywall)</p>
		<p class="mb-3">The Economist, &ldquo;The World in&nbsp;2017&rdquo;</p>
		<p>The Economist&rsquo;s special edition, The World in&nbsp;2017, contained predictions for the year ahead. Yuri&rsquo;s contribution discussed the high likelihood of&nbsp;major scientific breakthroughs in&nbsp;the coming year, and whether the general public would pay attention to&nbsp;them.</p>
	</div>

	<div class="mb-5">
		<p class="lead mb-3"><a href="https://www.edge.org/response-detail/27228" target="_blank">The Longevity Factor</a></p>
		<p class="mb-3">Edge Question 2017</p>
		<p>In&nbsp;2017 Yuri made his second contribution to&nbsp;the annual Edge question, considering the potential lifespan of&nbsp;our civilization and physical challenges to&nbsp;the survival of&nbsp;life in&nbsp;the far future of&nbsp;the Universe.</p>
	</div>

	<div class="mb-5">
		<p class="lead mb-3"><a href="https://www.edge.org/response-detail/26739" target="_blank">Tabby&rsquo;s Star</a></p>
		<p class="mb-3">Edge Question 2016</p>
		<p>In&nbsp;2016, Yuri contributed an&nbsp;article to&nbsp;the annual Edge question, looking at&nbsp;the recent excitement over the mysterious &ldquo;Tabby&rsquo;s Star,&rdquo; and the light it&nbsp;cast on&nbsp;astrobiology as&nbsp;a&nbsp;serious scientific field.</p>
	</div>

	<div class="mb-5">
		<p class="lead mb-3"><a href="https://breakthroughinitiatives.org/arewealone" target="_blank">SETI Open Letter</a></p>
		<p>In&nbsp;2015, Yuri joined a&nbsp;stellar group of&nbsp;scientists and intellectuals to&nbsp;sign an&nbsp;open letter about the importance of&nbsp;the search for life in&nbsp;the Universe. The letter appeared in&nbsp;the New York Times, the Guardian and [other publications].</p>
	</div>
	
</main>

